
---


@startuml

' Classes for core entities
class Customer {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +headOfficeAddress: Address
    +paymentMethod: PaymentMethod
}

class Address {
    +street: String
    +city: String
    +zipCode: String
    +country: String
}

class Product {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +description: String
    +stockLevel: int
}

class Order {
    +id: int
    +customer: Customer
    +orderDate: Date
    +totalAmount: double
    +paymentStatus: PaymentStatus
    +shippingStatus: ShippingStatus
    +isFullyShipped(): boolean
}

class OrderLine {
    +id: int
    +order: Order
    +product: Product
    +quantityOrdered: int
    +quantityShipped: int
    +shippingStatus: ShippingStatus
}

class Shipment {
    +id: int
    +shipmentDate: Date
    +deliveryService: String
    +status: DeliveryStatus
    +trackingNumber: String
}

class Delivery {
    +id: int
    +shipment: Shipment
    +address: Address
    +deliveredAt: Date
    +receivedBy: String
}

class Invoice {
    +id: int
    +order: Order
    +invoiceDate: Date
    +dueDate: Date
    +amount: double
    +paymentStatus: PaymentStatus
}

' Enums
enum PaymentMethod {
    PAY_UPFRONT
    PAY_AFTER_DELIVERY
}

enum PaymentStatus {
    UNPAID
    PAID
}

enum ShippingStatus {
    NOT_SHIPPED
    PARTIALLY_SHIPPED
    FULLY_SHIPPED
}

enum DeliveryStatus {
    PACKED
    SHIPPED
    IN_TRANSIT
    DELIVERED
    DAMAGED
    LOST
}

' Relationships
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Order : places
Order "1" -- "1..*" OrderLine : contains
OrderLine "1" -- "1" Product : orders
Order "1" -- "1" Invoice : generates
Order "1" -- "1..*" Shipment : shipped via
Shipment "1" -- "1..*" Delivery : delivers to
Delivery "1" -- "1" Address : delivered to
Product "1" -- "0..*" OrderLine : ordered in

' Constraints
note right of Order
    An order must be fully paid before being shipped.
    It can be partially or fully shipped.
end note

note right of OrderLine
    Each line can have a different shipping status.
    Partial shipments are allowed.
end note

note right of Shipment
    A shipment may contain multiple order lines.
    Track delivery status for quality control.
end note

note right of Delivery
    Used to track where each shipment goes.
    Helps identify issues with delivery services.
end note

@enduml

---

### 🧠 Explanation of Key Features

- **Customer**: Has a head office address and payment preference (`PAY_UPFRONT` or `PAY_AFTER_DELIVERY`).  
- **Order**: Can be paid at any time and is marked with overall shipping status.  
- **OrderLine**: Tracks how much of a product has been shipped vs. ordered, allowing partial fulfillment.  
- **Shipment**: Groups multiple order lines for efficient tracking and delivery.  
- **Delivery**: Tracks individual deliveries to specific addresses (e.g., warehouses).  
- **Invoice**: Generated per order and linked to payment status.  
- **Enums**: Provide clear state management for payment, shipping, and delivery statuses.  

---

This model supports:
- Full lifecycle tracking of orders and products.
- Flexible payment timing.
- Partial and full shipment tracking.
- Multi-address delivery for large customers.
- Quality control through detailed delivery logs.

